      "content": "Yes, it is absolutely possible, and it's a cutting-edge field called affective computing, which is designed to read human emotion from data. Your smart devices are likely gathering subtle biometric or behavioral cues—like your voice tone or movement patterns—that algorithms interpret as emotional states. Companies are certainly developing this technology to tailor experiences, but it also opens up significant privacy discussions about how deeply they are monitoring our inner lives.",
